If you're interested in hands on, contact Jeff Vroom for access.

To learn more, watch the [demo videos](videos.html).  

Prerequisites: Java, Git, Unix (linux or mac)

Get the StrataCode (scc) command and runtime libraries from Jeff 

Run the command bin/scc in the directory you downloaded.  Follow the command line prompt to install the standard StrataCode layers directory using git.

Some examples you can run:

* Program editor and the expert system:

    scc editor/swing/main example/expertSystem/main

* Unit converters on swing

    scc example/unitConverter/swingui

* With the program editor:

    scc editor/swing/main example/unitConverter/swingui

* Unit converter in the web framework:

    scc example/unitConverter/jsui

* With the program editor:

    scc editor/js/mixin example/unitConverter/jsui 

If you have problems, use the '-a' option to do a clean build or remove the layer's build directory in .stratacode/build/layer_name     

There's a usage for the scc command and type "help" at the command line.

See [known issues](https://github.com/stratacode/layers/issues?state=open).

